all folders are created in the comfy output path.
1 = output\date
2 = output\project name + num
3 = output\date\project name + num
4 = output\project name + num\date (project number should be set to fixed in this case)

to do a sequence of images in multible steps (300 f.e.):
- enter a value of 150 in the "Load-Cap"
- change the "Skip: Queue * Load-Cap" to increment, reset the value to 0
- enable extra options below the "Queue Prompt"
- change batch count to 2
- click queue prompt
(dont forget to reset the "Skip: Queue * Load-Cap" values on a new "project")

nodes.title: Notes
widgets_values:
Lower Denoise  = Closer to the video, mouth movement, blink, face, etc
Higher Denoise = Better representation of the provided image

Lower ControlNet = Better representation of the provided image
Higher ControlNet = Closer to the video, mouth movement, blink, face, etc.

the mimic/cfg mode on "DynamicThresholding" should be constant or the ksampler raises an error (sadly). i havent tested them all but half cos up and cos up dont work. :(

Noise 1 = Remove most noise
Noise 0.01 = a lot of noise

Use decent face images.

Use different IPAdapters & weights for style changes
 - IP Adapter Light can be a good choice, even at weight 1!
 - Disable "Image Crop Face" for non-face images

enter the path to your video (without quotes!)

dont delete show text, video dumb dont work without something connected to output_path for some reason.

it works for larger videos too (tested it with a 12min video 21598 frames) BUT you can't stop the progress by canceling the queue, the only way is to close the commandline window if you want to abort.

Skip Images: Value * Load Cap
increases the images to skip by value * load cap (set to increment and reset to 0 when restarting or choosing a new folder!)

0x50 = 0   read the first 50 Images skip = 0
1x50 = 50  read the 2nd 50 but skip the 1st 50
2x50 = 100 read the 3rd 50 but skip the first 100
3x50 = 150 read the 4th 50 but skip the first 150
etc.

Skip Images: Fixed Value ignores the above and skips the value number of images. Set to 0 to use the above Method.

if you want to test the controlnet preprocessor output, disable the ksampler in the fast bypasser.

the groups: "Folders" & "Input Values" should never be bypassed or muted.

if you want to save video frames disable everything listed in the fast groups bypasser except the mentioned groups above and enable "Save Video Frames", the output folder is what you setup in the group "Folders".

to use the face swap/restore on already rendered images disable everything listed in the fast groups bypasser except the mentioned groups above and enable load images, face swap and or face restore.

Dont forget to check the groups that you have enabled for those nodes you want to bypass before queuing. activating the controlnet group f.e. activates all controlnets...

For Face Swap and Restore you need the groups "Folders", "Input Values", "Load Images" and "Face Swap" and or "Face Restore".

for face swap use upper body or full body portraits. i tried to use a cropped face (like in IPAdapter) but the return msg was no face found, while upper body portraits always work, should be decent quality.

if you do this in several steps, i would suggest setting the project number to fixed so that all files are saved in the same directory.
Select the LoRA to add to the text
Select the Wildcard to add to the text
to ensure consistency across multiple images freeu is gone. say hello to StyleAligned Batch Align, this node is awesome.

the face detailer cannot process image batches, but it can process image lists. so it should not run with the model from animatediff, as there will only be noise in the face. this is because it only sends one image at a time through animatediff.

the first two upscalers must be 1x, otherwise the image would get bigger and bigger. 
1 x 1 x 4 = 4x (in this order, otherwise it would take ages until everyone is finished.)

with the following upscalers no additional sharpening is necessary, bypass the sharpen node if you dont want to use it:

1x artclarity
1x ITF-SkinDiffDetail-Lite-v1
4x UltraSharp/UltraFArt-v3-Fine

https://openmodeldb.info/models/1x-ArtClarity
https://openmodeldb.info/models/1x-ITF-SkinDiffDetail-Lite-v1
https://openmodeldb.info/models/4x-UltraSharp
https://openmodeldb.info/models/4x-UltraFArt-v3-Fine
https://openmodeldb.info/models/4x-Remacri
https://openmodeldb.info/models/4x-RealisticRescaler

the image is enlarged to 4x, then the face restorer is applied and only then is it scaled down. if you scale it down directly after the upscaler, the image quality is much worse.

you can find all kind of upscalers here:
https://openmodeldb.info/

more 1x
https://openmodeldb.info/models/1x-ITF-SkinDiffDDS-v1
https://openmodeldb.info/models/1x-HurrDeblur-SuperUltraCompact
https://openmodeldb.info/models/1x-Focus
https://openmodeldb.info/models/1x-Fatality-DeBlur
If the Face Restore node of mtb cannot be imported then delete everything in this group and the group itself. use Face Restore CF instead.
prompts everywhere should be outside the group in case the whole group is deactivated. since it is color bound it must have the same color as the ksampler and the face detailer.
Lineart + HED merged results in a better lineart of the subject (person, eyes and mimic), less background and harder lines.. unlike HED alone.
